courses.learning_outcomes:
Upon successful completion of this course, students should be able to:

Become acquainted with advanced skills necessary for conducting graduate research in the fields of biodiversity, environmental management, sustainability and related technologies, including laboratory management, information search, experimental design, presentation of research papers, writing of research proposal, thesis and scientific paper;

Apply central concepts in research ethics to ensure integrity and ethical compliance in all research endeavors.

● To understand basics of molecular biology;

● To know fundamentals of genome and genomics;

● To understand fundamentals and development of gene sequencing technology;

● To understand basic sequencing analysis;

● To gain practical experience in the frequently used tools of genomics

Upon successful completion of this course, students should be able to:

- understand key concepts in ecology and conservation;

- identify important questions and key issues in modern ecology and conservation;

- Apply scientific methods to issues relating to ecology and conservation;

- apply the concepts of experimental designs and hypothesis testing;

- find and collect information from research literature;

- critically analyse information from primary research literature;

- apply knowledge to real-world ecological and conservation issues and problems;

- recognise the scientific basis of global and regional ecological, environmental, and conservation problems

- appreciate the importance of biodiversity;

- develop a scientific perspective on major global issues (e.g. biodiversity crisis, climate change) and their potential solutions

Upon successful completion of this course, students should be able to:

- understand the theory and principles used in environmental impact assessment;

- identify the methods used to assess environmental impact such as habitat and protected species surveys;

- develop skills necessary of conducting effective environmental impact assessments;

- explain the implications and challenges of EIA processes.

Upon successful completion of this course, students should be able to:

- demonstrate in-depth knowledge and skills in scientific methods and research processes;

- develop competencies in finding, reading, and critically evaluating relevant scientific literatures;

- execute experiments and analyse data carefully;

- perform statistical analyses of data with good interpretations and discussion;

- master generic skills such as critical thinking and lifelong learning techniques;

- understand the importance of academic honesty.
